HEADWORD: Neurotome
<hw>Neu"ro*tome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Neurotomy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An instrument for cutting or
dissecting nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A neuromere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neurotomical</ent>⟦br⟧
